Sally' O's , has an Irish Pub atmosphere , but a Great little room to hear Americana Music Left side is the bar with their regular cast of characters ( Elvis, Cigar Store Indian, Bucky)  right side is the performance side with seating for maybe 30 , and Standing/Dancing space for another 15  Their regular bands are great ( Tom Hagerty , Les Sampou ,Patsy Hamel, Radioactive Rustlers, Stan Martin, One thin dime , Family Jewels ) each with their own favorites from the past and present they'll play for you . Weekend 6:00 early shows fit my Senior Schedule just fine thanks .  Stage is pretty small, but the sound system is GREAT , Dance floor  can get cramped on a hopping evening , but that's all part of the fun.  They have decent pub food at ok prices - Good Burgers 8$  ,  I don't drink, so the drinks are just drinks to me , but they seem to be good sized reasonably priced  The place is not too hard to find right on the one way part of Somerville Ave in Union Square ,  parking is usually available somewhere on the block , we never had any real trouble in this neighborhood , but we did get pulled over once by Somerville PD in a Pickup Truck  for... smoking Cigars in a MiniVan , No Charges Were Filed  ;-0)>
